.\" shorthand for double quote that works everywhere.
.ds q \N'34'
.TH VPRO __drivermansuffix__ __vendorversion__
.SH NAME
vpro \- SGI Odyssey (VPro) video driver
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B "Section \*qDevice\*q"
.BI "  Identifier \*q" devname \*q
.B "  Driver \*qvpro\*q"
\ \ ...
.B EndSection
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vpro
is an __xservername__ driver for the SGI Odyssey (VPro) graphics board
found in SGI Octane (IP30) workstations.
.PP
The Odyssey has no CPU-visible linear framebuffer; it is a dual-chip
OpenGL engine driven entirely through a command FIFO.  The driver renders
into a host-side shadow framebuffer and uploads dirty regions to the board
through the command FIFO.  It relies on the kernel
.B odyssey
fbdev driver to have set up the panel timing and to provide the
.B /dev/fbN
register mapping.
.SH SUPPORTED HARDWARE
.B vpro
supports the SGI Odyssey / VPro at its fixed 1280x1024 resolution in
24-bit TrueColor (stored as 32bpp).
.SH CONFIGURATION DETAILS
The
.B BusID
option selects which
.B /dev/fbN
device (and thus which board) to drive; it defaults to 0.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
__xservername__(__appmansuffix__), xorg.conf(__filemansuffix__),
Xserver(__appmansuffix__), X(__miscmansuffix__)
.SH AUTHORS
René Rebe.  Based on the xf86-video-impact driver by Peter Fuerst and on
the Linux odyssey fbdev driver by Stanislaw Skowronek, Johannes
Dickgreber, Joshua Kinard and René Rebe.
